label("$(-4,-3)$", (-4,-3), W);
[/asy]]So $m+n=4.8$, and $mn=-3$. Rewrite $m$ in terms of $n$. We get $m=4.8-n$. Substitute that into the product equation to get $-3=(4.8-n)n$. Expand and rearrange to get $n^2-4.8n-3=0$. By the quadratic formula we find $n=2.4\pm\sqrt{2.4^2+3}$. So $m=2.4\pm\sqrt{2.4^2+3}$ as well. $m-n=4.8-4.8=8.\tag*{$\blacksquare$}</answer>

